Caec. xiv. 39 eadem ui et isdem armis mihi ante occurratur, ne non modo intrare, uerum adspicere aut adspirare possim. Two causes are assigned for the intermittent violence of Aetna, (1) an accumulation of rock which blocks up the passage at the bottorn and keeps the winds imprisoned under it 3 (2) a similar obstruction which meets the winds on their way downwards.
